label.value: abnormal membrane lipid distribution

value.value: A localization phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which the distribution of one or more lipids in a cellular membrane is abnormal.

label.value: normal membrane lipid distribution

value.value: A localization phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which the distribution of one or more lipids in a cellular membrane is normal (i.e. indistinguishable from wild type).

label.value: abnormal plasma membrane phosphatidylserine distribution resulting in decreased concentration at cell tip

value.value: A localization phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which the distribution of phosphatidylserine (PS) in the plasma membrane is abnormal such that the PS level is lower than normal at one or both cell tips. Normally, PS shows a polarized distribution with a higher concentration at the cell tips than in the lateral plasma membrane.

label.value: increased gene expression

value.value: A cellular process phenotype in which gene expression occurs to a greater extent than normal. One or more parts of gene expression, such as transcription or translation, may be affected, and all genes, or a specific subset of genes, may be affected.

label.value: decreased gene expression

value.value: A cellular process phenotype in which gene expression occurs to a lower extent than normal. One or more parts of gene expression, such as transcription or translation, may be affected, and all genes, or a specific subset of genes, may be affected.

label.value: decreased gene expression during nitrogen starvation

value.value: A cellular process phenotype in which gene expression occurs to a lower extent than normal when the cell is subject to nitrogen starvation. One or more parts of gene expression, such as transcription or translation, may be affected, and all genes, or a specific subset of genes, may be affected.

label.value: abnormal gene expression

value.value: A cellular process phenotype in which gene expression is abnormal. One or more parts of gene expression, such as transcription or translation, may be affected, and all genes, or a specific subset of genes, may be affected.

label.value: increased protein localization to cytoplasm

value.value: A cell phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which the localization of a protein to the cytoplasm is increased.

definition.value: We recommend noting which protein(s) were used in the assay when annotating to this term.

label.value: normal protein localization to nucleus

value.value: A cell phenotype in which the localization of a protein to the nucleus is normal (i.e. indistinguishable from wild type).

definition.value: We recommend noting which protein(s) were used in the assay when annotating to this term.

label.value: normal protein localization to nucleus during nitrogen starvation

value.value: A cell phenotype in which the localization of a protein to the nucleus is normal (i.e. indistinguishable from wild type) when the cell is subject to nitrogen starvation.

definition.value: We recommend noting which protein(s) were used in the assay when annotating to this term.

label.value: abnormal multiple protein binding to DNA

value.value: A molecular function phenotype in which the binding of two or more proteins to DNA is abnormal. The proteins may bind simultaneously or sequentially, but both or all would normally be present together on DNA at some time. One affected gene product may be encoded by the mutated gene, or all may be encoded by different genes.

label.value: inviable elongated tetranucleate triseptate vegetative cell, single septa between nuclei

value.value: A cell morphology phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which a cell is inviable, is elongated, has four nuclei and three septa, and the septa are not grouped together, but are located so as to form separate compartments with a single nucleus in each.

label.value: abolished cell separation after cytokinesis

value.value: A cellular process phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which cell separation after cytokinesis does not occur.

label.value: abolished septum disassembly

value.value: A cellular process phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which septum disassembly does not occur.

label.value: delayed onset of mitotic spindle disassembly

value.value: A cellular process phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which mitotic spindle disassembly begins later than normal.

label.value: decreased protein kinase activity during mitotic G1 phase

value.value: A molecular function phenotype in which the observed rate of a protein kinase activity is decreased during the G1 phase of the mitotic cell cycle.

label.value: normal CDK-cyclin complex binding during mitotic G1 phase

value.value: A molecular function phenotype in which the binding of one protein to a CDK-cyclin complex is normal (i.e. indistinguishable from wild type) during the G1 phase of the mitotic cell cycle. The protein whose binding to the CDK-cyclin complex is assayed may be encoded by the mutated gene, or may be encoded by a different gene.

definition.value: This term can be used for any interaction with a protein complex that is assayed in a mutant, whether or not the mutated gene product is one of the interacting proteins. We recommend noting which proteins were used in the assay when annotating to this term.

label.value: increased RNA level during mitotic G2 phase

value.value: A cell phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which the amount of RNA measured in a cell during G2 phase of the mitotic cell cycle is higher than normal. Total RNA or a specific RNA may be affected.

definition.value: Consider annotating to a term describing abnormal transcription or abnormal regulation of transcription, but note that changes in RNA levels may result from changes in RNA stability as well as changes in transcription. We recommend noting which RNA(s) were used in the assay when annotating to this term.

label.value: abolished MBF complex assembly during mitotic G1 phase

value.value: A cellular process phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which MBF complex assembly is abolished during G1 phase of the mitotic cell cycle.

label.value: sensitive to ethanol in stationary phase

value.value: A phenotype in which cells show increased sensitivity to ethanol when the cell population is in stationary phase. Cells stop growing (and may die) at a concentration of ethanol that allows wild type cells to grow.

label.value: normal viability upon phosphate starvation

value.value: A cell population phenotype in which a normal proportion of cells in the population remains viable under conditions of phosphate starvation.

definition.value: Use this term to annotate experiments in which a culture is grown to stationary phase under phosphate-depleted conditions, and then the number of cells viable enough to form a colony upon return to conditions supporting vegetative growth is measured and compared to wild type.

label.value: normal viability upon sulfur starvation

value.value: A cell population phenotype in which a normal proportion of cells in the population remains viable under conditions of sulfur starvation.

definition.value: Use this term to annotate experiments in which a culture is grown to stationary phase under sulfur-depleted conditions, and then the number of cells viable enough to form a colony upon return to conditions supporting vegetative growth is measured and compared to wild type.

label.value: abnormal DNA repair

value.value: A cellular process phenotype in which DNA repair is abnormal.

label.value: abnormal meiotic mismatch repair

value.value: A cellular process phenotype in which meiotic mismatch repair is abnormal. Meiotic mismatch repair is the identification and correction of base-base mismatches, small insertion-deletion loops, and regions of heterology that are present in duplex DNA formed with strands from two recombining molecules.

label.value: normal DNA repair

value.value: A cellular process phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which DNA repair is normal (i.e. indistinguishable from wild type).

label.value: normal UV-damage excision repair

value.value: A cellular process phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which UV-damage excision repair is normal (i.e. indistinguishable from wild type). UV-damage excision repair is a DNA repair process that is initiated by an endonuclease that introduces a single-strand incision immediately 5' of a UV-induced damage site, and that acts on both cyclobutane pyrimidine dimers (CPDs) and pyrimidine-pyrimidone 6-4 photoproducts (6-4PPs).

label.value: increased cyclin-dependent protein kinase activity during cellular response to pheromone

value.value: A molecular function phenotype in which the observed rate of a cyclin-dependent protein kinase activity is increased during a cellular response to a pheromone.

label.value: abolished protein degradation during cellular response to pheromone

value.value: A cellular process phenotype in which protein degradation does not occur during a cellular response to a pheromone. Protein degradation, also known as protein catabolism, is any metabolic process that results in the destruction of the native, active configuration of a protein, with or without the hydrolysis of peptide bonds.

definition.value: We recommend noting which protein(s) were used in the assay when annotating to this term.

label.value: normal protein level during cellular response to pheromone

value.value: A cell phenotype in which the amount of protein measured in a cell during a cellular response to a pheromone is normal (i.e. indistinguishable from wild type). Total protein or a specific protein may be affected.

definition.value: We recommend noting which protein(s) were used in the assay when annotating to this term.

label.value: normal RNA level during cellular response to pheromone

value.value: A cell phenotype in which the amount of RNA measured in a cell during a cellular response to a pheromone is normal (i.e. indistinguishable from wild type). Total RNA or a specific RNA may be affected.

definition.value: We recommend noting which RNA(s) were used in the assay when annotating to this term.

label.value: abnormal negative regulation of mitotic DNA replication initiation resulting in complete rereplication, with otherwise normal S phase

value.value: A regulation phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which abnormal negative regulation of the initiation of mitotic DNA replication results in one or more rounds of rereplication of the entire genome, but takes place during S phases that appear nearly normal apart from occurring without intervening mitoses. Origin usage is normal, rounds of DNA synthesis are correlated with G1/S phase gene expression and cell mass increase, and the genome is replicated evenly.

label.value: abnormal negative regulation of mitotic DNA replication initiation resulting in complete rereplication, with abnormal S phase

value.value: A regulation phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which abnormal negative regulation of the initiation of mitotic DNA replication results in one or more rounds of rereplication of the entire genome, and other features of S phase are abnormal. Rounds of replication are not correlated with G1/S phase gene expression, and origin usage is altered.

label.value: increased cellular P(1),P(4)-bis(5'-adenosyl) tetraphosphate level

value.value: A cell phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which the amount of P(1),P(4)-bis(5'-adenosyl) tetraphosphate (Ap4A) measured in a cell is higher than normal.

label.value: normal mitotic G2 DNA damage checkpoint

value.value: A cell cycle checkpoint phenotype in which the mitotic G2 DNA damage checkpoint is normal (i.e. indistinguishable from wild type). The mitotic G2 DNA damage checkpoint negatively regulates progression through the G2/M transition of the mitotic cell cycle in response to DNA damage.

label.value: sensitive to manganese

value.value: A phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which cells show increased sensitivity to manganese. Cells stop growing (and may die) at a concentration of manganese ions that allows wild type cells to grow.

label.value: resistance to amiodarone

value.value: An increased chemical resistance phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which cells grow in the presence of a higher concentration of amiodarone than normal.

label.value: sensitive to fenpropimorph

value.value: A phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which cells show increased sensitivity to fenpropimorph. Cells stop growing (and may die) at a concentration of fenpropimorph that allows wild type cells to grow.

label.value: decreased bis(5'-nucleosyl)-tetraphosphatase (asymmetrical) activity

value.value: A molecular function phenotype in which the observed rate of bis(5'-nucleosyl)-tetraphosphatase (asymmetrical) activity is decreased.

label.value: decreased protein localization to nuclear periphery during mitotic interphase

value.value: A cell phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which the localization of a protein to the nuclear periphery is decreased during interphase of the mitotic cell cycle. The nuclear periphery is the portion of the nuclear lumen proximal to the inner nuclear membrane.

definition.value: We recommend noting which protein(s) were used in the assay when annotating to this term.

label.value: abnormal protein localization to shmoo tip membrane

value.value: A cell phenotype in which the localization of a protein to the plasma membrane at the tip of a shmoo, or mating projection, is abnormal.

definition.value: We recommend noting which protein(s) were used in the assay when annotating to this term.

label.value: abolished protein localization to shmoo tip membrane, with protein mislocalized to endoplasmic reticulum

value.value: A cell phenotype in which the localization of a protein to the plasma membrane at the tip of a shmoo, or mating projection, is abolished, and the protein is present in the endoplasmic reticulum instead.

definition.value: We recommend noting which protein(s) were used in the assay when annotating to this term.

label.value: abolished protein localization to shmoo tip membrane, with protein distributed in plasma membrane

value.value: A cell phenotype in which the localization of a protein to the plasma membrane at the tip of a shmoo, or mating projection, is abolished, and the protein is instead detected distributed over a greater area of the plasma membrane than normal.

definition.value: We recommend noting which protein(s) were used in the assay when annotating to this term.

label.value: decreased protein localization to shmoo tip membrane

value.value: A cell phenotype in which the localization of a protein to the plasma membrane at the tip of a shmoo, or mating projection, is decreased.

definition.value: We recommend noting which protein(s) were used in the assay when annotating to this term.

label.value: decreased protein localization to shmoo tip membrane, with protein mislocalized to endoplasmic reticulum

value.value: A cell phenotype in which the localization of a protein to the plasma membrane at the tip of a shmoo, or mating projection, is decreased, and some of the protein is present in the endoplasmic reticulum instead.

definition.value: We recommend noting which protein(s) were used in the assay when annotating to this term.

label.value: decreased protein localization to shmoo tip membrane, with protein distributed in plasma membrane

value.value: A cell phenotype in which the localization of a protein to the plasma membrane at the tip of a shmoo, or mating projection, is decreased, and some of the protein is instead detected distributed over a greater area of the plasma membrane than normal.

definition.value: We recommend noting which protein(s) were used in the assay when annotating to this term.

label.value: protein mislocalized to endoplasmic reticulum

value.value: A cell phenotype in which a protein that is not normally found in the endoplasmic reticulum is observed there.

definition.value: Note that this term can be used to annotate any case where a protein is found in the ER in a mutant, but not in wild type. In some cases, there may be enough additional information to annotate to 'abnormal protein localization' (FYPO:0000443) or one of its descendants. We recommend noting which protein(s) were used in the assay when annotating to this term.

label.value: increased DNA damage during mitotic S phase

value.value: A cell phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which the amount of DNA damage measured in a cell during S phase of the mitotic cell cycle is greater than normal. The number, extent, or both of damage sites may be increased.

label.value: monopolar mitotic spindle nucleated from old spindle pole body

value.value: A physical cellular phenotype in which the mitotic spindle forms with microtubules emanating from only one pole, nucleated from the old spindle pole body.

label.value: decreased mitotic spindle microtubule nucleation from spindle pole body

value.value: A microtubule cytoskeleton organization phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which nucleation of spindle microtubules from the spindle pole body (SPB) occurs to a lesser extent than normal.

label.value: normal gamma-tubulin complex localization to mitotic spindle pole body

value.value: A cell phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which localization of the gamma-tubulin complex to the spindle pole body is normal (i.e. indistinguishable from wild type).
